FreePiano 2.1
; keypiano default keymap — QWERTY, two chromatic octaves (C4–B5)
; White keys: Z-M row (octave 4), Q-U row (octave 5)
; Black keys sit ABOVE the gap between their two white keys, matching a real
;   piano: C#=S (between Z/X), D#=D, F#=G, G#=H, A#=J  (octave 4)
;          C#=2 (between Q/W), D#=3, F#=5, G#=6, A#=7  (octave 5)
; F1/F2 = octave down/up  |  Space = sustain

; ── Octave 4 – white keys (Z row) ────────────────────────────────────────────
Keydown Z Note In_0 C4
Label Z Z
Keydown X Note In_0 D4
Label X X
Keydown C Note In_0 E4
Label C C
Keydown V Note In_0 F4
Label V V
Keydown B Note In_0 G4
Label B B
Keydown N Note In_0 A4
Label N N
Keydown M Note In_0 B4
Label M M

; ── Octave 4 – black keys (home row, above the gap between white keys) ───────
Keydown S Note In_0 C#4
Label S S
Keydown D Note In_0 Eb4
Label D D
Keydown G Note In_0 F#4
Label G G
Keydown H Note In_0 Ab4
Label H H
Keydown J Note In_0 Bb4
Label J J

; ── Octave 5 – white keys (Q row) ────────────────────────────────────────────
Keydown Q Note In_0 C5
Label Q Q
Keydown W Note In_0 D5
Label W W
Keydown E Note In_0 E5
Label E E
Keydown R Note In_0 F5
Label R R
Keydown T Note In_0 G5
Label T T
Keydown Y Note In_0 A5
Label Y Y
Keydown U Note In_0 B5
Label U U

; ── Octave 5 – black keys (number row, above the gap between white keys) ──────
Keydown 2 Note In_0 C#5
Label 2 2
Keydown 3 Note In_0 Eb5
Label 3 3
Keydown 5 Note In_0 F#5
Label 5 5
Keydown 6 Note In_0 Ab5
Label 6 6
Keydown 7 Note In_0 Bb5
Label 7 7

; ── Controls ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Keydown F1 Octave In_0 Dec 1
Label F1 Oct-
Keydown F2 Octave In_0 Inc 1
Label F2 Oct+
Keydown Space Sustain In_0 Set 127
Label Space Sus
